/-- Sprint F2i-3o-2b: components of the outer forest `r.1.1.1` whose
canonical star vertex lies inside `őī.vertices`.  These are the "promoted"
components: the ones whose internal edges must be retained inside the
forest-cover source subgraph, so that the quotient-remainder subtraction
`(ő≥.internalEdges - A.internalEdges)` cancels them exactly. -/
private noncomputable def forestQuotientForestSigmaForestCoverPromotedComponents
    [IsDivergencePreservedByAdmissibleForestContract]
    (g : HopfGen)
    (r : {r : forestQuotientForestSigma g //
      r ‚ąą forestQuotientForestSigmaIndex g})
    (őī : FeynmanSubgraph (forestOuterActualQuotientGraph g r.1.1)) :
    Finset (FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph) :=
