/-
Deprecated connected-only route.

The block below was the original proper-connected-subgraph coassociativity
attempt.  It is intentionally no longer compiled: the active H5.8F proof above
uses the admissible-forest `ŌÜ` reindexing route, while this older route stops
at the star-free RHS obstruction noted at the end of the block.  Keeping it in
one comment preserves the design record without making the elaborator revisit
the obsolete tensor expansions.

/-! ### Stage 3a-i ‚ÄĒ LHS expand

The LHS is `assoc ((őĒ ‚äó id) (őĒ (X g)))`. Stage 2's expand of `őĒ(X g)`
gives 3 terms; distributing `(őĒ ‚äó id)` and `assoc` and re-expanding the
inner `őĒ` produces 7 distinct shapes:

```
(a) X g ‚äó (1 ‚äó 1)                                    ‚ÄĒ pure boundary
(b) 1 ‚äó (X g ‚äó 1)                                    ‚ÄĒ pure boundary
(c) ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó ([őď/ő≥] ‚äó 1)                            ‚ÄĒ sum √ó right-1
(d) 1 ‚äó (1 ‚äó X g)                                    ‚ÄĒ pure boundary (from őĒ(1))
(e‚āĀ) ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó (1 ‚äó [őď/ő≥])                           ‚ÄĒ őĒ([ő≥])-boundary 1
(e‚āā) ő£_ő≥ 1 ‚äó ([ő≥] ‚äó [őď/ő≥])                           ‚ÄĒ őĒ([ő≥])-boundary 2
(e‚āÉ) ő£_ő≥ ő£_{ő≥'‚ääő≥} [ő≥'] ‚äó ([ő≥/ő≥'] ‚äó [őď/ő≥])           ‚ÄĒ main double sum (Stage 3b target)
```

We collect (a)+(b)+(d) as the 3 pure boundaries. (c)+(e‚āĀ)+(e‚āā) are
"mixed" boundary-times-sum terms. (e‚āÉ) is the only doubly-indexed sum. -/

/-! #### Per-term abbreviations to avoid `if-then-else` parsing ambiguity

Each of the 6 LHS shapes is given a private name. The full LHS is then
their sum, written with explicit grouping. -/

/-- (a) Pure `X g ‚äó (1 ‚äó 1)`. -/
private noncomputable def termA (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))

/-- (b) Pure `1 ‚äó (X g ‚äó 1)`. -/
private noncomputable def termB (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))

/-- (d) Pure `1 ‚äó (1 ‚äó X g)`. -/
private noncomputable def termD (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH))

/-- (c) Mixed `ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó ([őď/ő≥] ‚äó 1)`. -/
private noncomputable def termC (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
    if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
      let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
      ((gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
        ((gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
          (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)))
    else 0

/-- (e) Aggregate of (e‚āĀ)+(e‚āā)+(e‚āÉ): the part of the LHS where the
inner `őĒ` was applied to `[ő≥]` (left factor). Kept as
`ő£_ő≥ assoc (őĒ([ő≥]) ‚äó [őď/ő≥])` for now; further expanded in later stages. -/
private noncomputable def termE (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
    if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
      let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
      (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
        ((coproduct_strict (gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1))) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
          (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
            (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne)))
    else 0

/-- LHS expand ‚ÄĒ sum of 5 per-term components. -/
private theorem coassoc_LHS_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
        ((Algebra.TensorProduct.map coproduct_strict (AlgHom.id ‚Ąö HopfH))
          (coproduct_strict (MvPolynomial.X g))) =
      termA g + termB g + termC g + termD g + termE g := by
  -- Step 1: expand őĒ(X g) once via Stage 2.
  rw [coproduct_strict_X_eq g]
  -- Step 2: distribute (map őĒ id) and assoc through the additive structure.
  simp only [map_add, Algebra.TensorProduct.map_tmul, AlgHom.coe_id, id_eq,
    map_one, map_sum]
  -- Step 3: expand őĒ(X g) (left-most term) once more via Stage 2,
  -- then distribute (¬∑ ‚äó 1) through the inner +.
  rw [coproduct_strict_X_eq g]
  simp only [TensorProduct.add_tmul, TensorProduct.sum_tmul, map_add, map_sum]
  -- Step 4: split őĒ(1) ‚äó X g via one_def.
  rw [show ((1 : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH))
        = ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) from by
      rw [Algebra.TensorProduct.one_def]]
  -- Step 5: rewrite the (c)-style sum's body via Finset.sum_congr +
  -- assoc_tmul + if-zero handling. The first sum gets `(...)‚äó1` form;
  -- the second sum keeps its `(map őĒ id) (...)` form (becomes termE).
  rw [show (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
          ((if hő≥ : x.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < x.internalEdges.card then
              (gen (x.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                (gen (x.contractToHopfGen
                  (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1
                  (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2)))
            else 0) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))) = termC g from ?cEq]
  case cEq =>
    unfold termC
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro x _
    split_ifs with hő≥
    ¬∑ exact Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc_tmul (R := ‚Ąö) (S := ‚Ąö) (T := ‚Ąö)
        (A := HopfH) (C := HopfH) (D := HopfH) _ _ _
    ¬∑ simp [TensorProduct.zero_tmul]
  -- The remaining second sum is exactly termE.
  rw [show (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
          ((Algebra.TensorProduct.map coproduct_strict (AlgHom.id ‚Ąö HopfH))
            (if h : x.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < x.internalEdges.card then
              (gen (x.toHopfGen h.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                gen (x.contractToHopfGen
                  (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) h.1
                  (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos h.2))
            else 0))) = termE g from ?eEq]
  case eEq =>
    unfold termE
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro x _
    split_ifs with hő≥
    ¬∑ simp [Algebra.TensorProduct.map_tmul]
    ¬∑ simp
  -- Apply assoc_tmul on the three pure-tmul boundaries.
  -- The two pure-tmul reductions are:
  --   assoc (X g ‚äó 1 ‚äó 1) = X g ‚äó (1 ‚äó 1)  = termA g
  --   assoc (1 ‚äó X g ‚äó 1) = 1 ‚äó (X g ‚äó 1)  = termB g
  --   assoc (1 ‚äó 1 ‚äó X g) = 1 ‚äó (1 ‚äó X g)  = termD g
  unfold termA termB termD
  rw [show (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
        ((MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)) =
      (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))
      from Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc_tmul (R := ‚Ąö) (S := ‚Ąö) (T := ‚Ąö)
        (A := HopfH) (C := HopfH) (D := HopfH) _ _ _]
  rw [show (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
        ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)) =
      (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))
      from Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc_tmul (R := ‚Ąö) (S := ‚Ąö) (T := ‚Ąö)
        (A := HopfH) (C := HopfH) (D := HopfH) _ _ _]
  rw [show (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
        ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH)) =
      (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH))
      from Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc_tmul (R := ‚Ąö) (S := ‚Ąö) (T := ‚Ąö)
        (A := HopfH) (C := HopfH) (D := HopfH) _ _ _]

/-! ### Stage 3a-ii ‚ÄĒ RHS expand

The RHS is `(map id őĒ) (őĒ (X g))`. Stage 2's expand of `őĒ(X g)` gives
3 terms; distributing `(map id őĒ)` produces:

```
(a') X g ‚äó őĒ(1) = X g ‚äó (1 ‚äó 1)                         = termA g
(b') 1 ‚äó őĒ(X g) = 1 ‚äó (X g ‚äó 1 + 1 ‚äó X g + ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó [őď/ő≥])
   = 1 ‚äó (X g ‚äó 1)                                       = termB g
   + 1 ‚äó (1 ‚äó X g)                                       = termD g
   + ő£_ő≥ 1 ‚äó ([ő≥] ‚äó [őď/ő≥])                              = termE2 g
(f') ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó őĒ([őď/ő≥])                                  = termF g  (Stage 3b target)
```

So `RHS = termA g + termB g + termD g + termE2 g + termF g`.

Note: LHS's termC (= ő£ [ő≥] ‚äó ([őď/ő≥] ‚äó 1)) and termE1 (= ő£ [ő≥] ‚äó (1 ‚äó [őď/ő≥]))
are **inside** termF g (after expanding őĒ([őď/ő≥]) once). The bijection
in Stage 3b/3c reorganizes termF to match LHS's termC + termE1 + (e‚āÉ). -/

/-- (e‚āā from LHS, also second-level term for RHS) `ő£_ő≥ 1 ‚äó ([ő≥] ‚äó [őď/ő≥])`. -/
private noncomputable def termE2 (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
    if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
      let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
      ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
        ((gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
          (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
            (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne) : HopfH)))
    else 0

/-- (f') `ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó őĒ([őď/ő≥])` ‚ÄĒ RHS-only aggregate, expanded later. -/
private noncomputable def termF (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
    if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
      let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
      ((gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
        (coproduct_strict (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
          (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne))))
    else 0

/-- RHS expand ‚ÄĒ sum of 5 per-term components. -/
private theorem coassoc_RHS_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    (Algebra.TensorProduct.map (AlgHom.id ‚Ąö HopfH) coproduct_strict)
        (coproduct_strict (MvPolynomial.X g)) =
      termA g + termB g + termD g + termE2 g + termF g := by
  -- Step 1: expand őĒ(X g) once via Stage 2.
  rw [coproduct_strict_X_eq g]
  -- Step 2: distribute (map id őĒ) through the additive structure.
  simp only [map_add, Algebra.TensorProduct.map_tmul, AlgHom.coe_id, id_eq,
    map_one, map_sum]
  -- Now we have:
  --   (X g ‚äó őĒ(1)) + (1 ‚äó őĒ(X g)) + ő£_ő≥ if hő≥ then [ő≥] ‚äó őĒ([őď/ő≥]) else 0
  -- = (X g ‚äó 1) + (1 ‚äó őĒ(X g)) + termF g (the last is termF after if-zero handling)
  -- where őĒ(1) = 1.
  -- Step 3: expand the inner őĒ(X g) (in 1 ‚äó őĒ(X g)) via Stage 2.
  rw [coproduct_strict_X_eq g]
  -- Now: (X g ‚äó 1) + (1 ‚äó (X g ‚äó 1 + 1 ‚äó X g + ő£_ő≥ ...)) + ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó őĒ([őď/ő≥])
  -- Distribute (1 ‚äó ¬∑) through the inner +.
  simp only [TensorProduct.tmul_add, TensorProduct.tmul_sum, map_add, map_sum]
  -- Step 4: split (X g ‚äó 1) where the "1" is in HopfH ‚äó HopfH; it should be 1 ‚äó 1.
  rw [show ((MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH))
        = (MvPolynomial.X g : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)) from by
      rw [Algebra.TensorProduct.one_def]]
  -- Step 5: handle the (e‚āā) sum: `ő£ if hő≥ then 1 ‚äó ([ő≥] ‚äó [őď/ő≥]) else 0` = termE2 g
  rw [show (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
          (if hő≥ : x.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < x.internalEdges.card then
              (gen (x.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                gen (x.contractToHopfGen
                  (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1
                  (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2))
            else 0))) = termE2 g from ?e2Eq]
  case e2Eq =>
    unfold termE2
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro x _
    split_ifs with hő≥
    ¬∑ rfl
    ¬∑ simp [TensorProduct.tmul_zero]
  -- Step 6: handle the (f) sum: `ő£ if hő≥ then [ő≥] ‚äó őĒ([őď/ő≥]) else 0` = termF g
  rw [show (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        (Algebra.TensorProduct.map (AlgHom.id ‚Ąö HopfH) coproduct_strict)
          (if h : x.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < x.internalEdges.card then
              (gen (x.toHopfGen h.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                gen (x.contractToHopfGen
                  (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) h.1
                  (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos h.2))
            else 0)) = termF g from ?fEq]
  case fEq =>
    unfold termF
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro x _
    split_ifs with hő≥
    ¬∑ simp [Algebra.TensorProduct.map_tmul]
    ¬∑ simp
  -- Now both sides are sums of identical shapes.
  unfold termA termB termD
  abel

/-! ### Stage 3a-iii ‚ÄĒ termE and termF further expansion

`termE g = ő£_ő≥ assoc (őĒ([ő≥]) ‚äó [őď/ő≥])` ‚ÄĒ expand őĒ([ő≥]) once more.
`termF g = ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó őĒ([őď/ő≥])` ‚ÄĒ expand őĒ([őď/ő≥]) once more.

Each yields 3 sub-terms. Several are duplicates between LHS/RHS,
allowing cancellation; the genuine bijection lives only in the
double-sum termE3 ‚ÜĒ termF3 part. -/

/-- (e‚āĀ) `ő£_ő≥ [ő≥] ‚äó (1 ‚äó [őď/ő≥])`. Symmetric to termE2. -/
private noncomputable def termE1 (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
    if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
      let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
      ((gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
        ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
          (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
            (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne) : HopfH)))
    else 0

/-- (e‚āÉ) Double sum: `ő£_ő≥ ő£_{ő≥'‚ääő≥} [ő≥'] ‚äó ([ő≥/ő≥'] ‚äó [őď/ő≥])`.
Concretely: the third (sum) part of `coproduct_strict (gen ő≥.toHopfGen)`
crossed with `[őď/ő≥]`, then assoc'd. -/
private noncomputable def termE3 (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
    if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
      let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
      (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
        ((coproduct_strict (gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1))
          - (gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))
          - ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1))) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
          (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
            (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne) : HopfH))
    else 0

/-- (f‚āÉ) Double sum: `ő£_ő≥ ő£_{ő≥''‚ääőď/ő≥} [ő≥] ‚äó ([ő≥''] ‚äó [(őď/ő≥)/ő≥''])`.
Concretely: `[ő≥]` crossed with the sum part of `coproduct_strict (gen ő≥.contractToHopfGen)`. -/
private noncomputable def termF3 (g : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH) :=
  ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
    if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
      let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
      let ő≥c := ő≥.contractToHopfGen
        (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne
      ((gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
        (coproduct_strict (gen ő≥c)
          - ((gen ő≥c : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))
          - ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (gen ő≥c : HopfH))))
    else 0

/-- Stage 3a-iii: termE expand into termE1 + termE2 + termE3. -/
private theorem termE_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    termE g = termE1 g + termE2 g + termE3 g := by
  unfold termE termE1 termE2 termE3
  rw [‚Üź Finset.sum_add_distrib, ‚Üź Finset.sum_add_distrib]
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥ _
  split_ifs with hő≥
  ¬∑ -- For each ő≥: assoc (őĒ([ő≥]) ‚äó [őď/ő≥]) = (e‚āĀ) + (e‚āā) + (e‚āÉ) per ő≥.
    -- Eliminate the let-binding `hő≥Ne` (zeta-reduce) and abbreviate
    -- the two recurring `gen` values without using `set` (which doesn't
    -- traverse `have`-bindings reliably here).
    simp only []
    -- Now both sides are uniform; use linearity of assoc + sub_tmul
    -- to absorb the subtraction term and apply assoc_tmul on each piece.
    rw [show ‚ąÄ X : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH, ‚ąÄ a c : HopfH,
          (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
            ((X - (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)) - ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] a)) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c) =
          (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom (X ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c)
            - (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c))
            - ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c)) from ?subAux]
    case subAux =>
      intro X a c
      rw [TensorProduct.sub_tmul, TensorProduct.sub_tmul, map_sub, map_sub]
      -- After sub distribution, the remaining `assoc (a ‚äó 1 ‚äó c)` and
      -- `assoc (1 ‚äó a ‚äó c)` reduce by assoc_tmul.
      rw [show (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
            (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c) = a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c)
          from Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc_tmul (R := ‚Ąö) (S := ‚Ąö) (T := ‚Ąö)
            (A := HopfH) (C := HopfH) (D := HopfH) a 1 c]
      rw [show (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
            ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c) = (1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c)
          from Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc_tmul (R := ‚Ąö) (S := ‚Ąö) (T := ‚Ąö)
            (A := HopfH) (C := HopfH) (D := HopfH) 1 a c]
    abel
  ¬∑ simp

/-- Stage 3a-iii: termF expand into termC + termE1 + termF3. -/
private theorem termF_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    termF g = termC g + termE1 g + termF3 g := by
  unfold termF termC termE1 termF3
  rw [‚Üź Finset.sum_add_distrib, ‚Üź Finset.sum_add_distrib]
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥ _
  split_ifs with hő≥
  ¬∑ -- Goal: a ‚äó coproduct_strict c =
    --        (a ‚äó (c ‚äó 1)) + (a ‚äó (1 ‚äó c))
    --      + (a ‚äó (coproduct_strict c - c ‚äó 1 - 1 ‚äó c))
    -- by tmul-linearity in the right factor.
    simp only []
    rw [show ‚ąÄ a c : HopfH,
          (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (coproduct_strict c -
              (c ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)) - ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c))
            : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] (HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH)) =
          (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] coproduct_strict c)
            - (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (c ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH)))
            - (a ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] c)) from ?subAux]
    case subAux =>
      intro a c
      rw [TensorProduct.tmul_sub, TensorProduct.tmul_sub]
    abel
  ¬∑ simp

/-! ### Stage 3b ‚ÄĒ termE3 and termF3 inner-sum expansion

We expand the inner `coproduct_strict (gen ...)` in both termE3 and
termF3 via `coproduct_strict_X_eq`, removing boundary terms and
exposing the genuine double-sum structure.

The result is two double sums indexed by chains `(ő≥_outer, ő≥_inner)`
that turn out to be in bijection (Stage 3b proper). -/

/-- Helper: the sum part of `coproduct_strict (X h)`, i.e.
`coproduct_strict (X h) - (X h ‚äó 1) - (1 ‚äó X h)`. By Stage 2 this
equals the proper-divergent-subgraph sum. -/
private noncomputable def coproductGen_sumPart (h : HopfGen) : HopfH ‚äó[‚Ąö] HopfH :=
  coproduct_strict (MvPolynomial.X h)
    - ((MvPolynomial.X h : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (1 : HopfH))
    - ((1 : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö] (MvPolynomial.X h : HopfH))

/-- The `coproductGen_sumPart` equals the proper-divergent-subgraph sum. -/
private theorem coproductGen_sumPart_eq (h : HopfGen) :
    coproductGen_sumPart h =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG h).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
          (gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
            (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
              (repG_wellFormed h) (repG_isOnePI h) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne) : HopfH)
        else 0 := by
  unfold coproductGen_sumPart
  rw [coproduct_strict_X_eq h]
  abel

/-- termE3 expanded as a sum over `ő≥_outer` of `gen ő≥` is replaced by
`coproductGen_sumPart`-driven inner sum. -/
private theorem termE3_eq_sumPart (g : HopfGen) :
    termE3 g =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
          (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
            ((coproductGen_sumPart (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1)) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
              (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
                (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne) : HopfH))
        else 0 := by
  unfold termE3 coproductGen_sumPart
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥ _
  split_ifs with hő≥
  ¬∑ -- gen h = MvPolynomial.X h, so coproduct_strict (gen h) = coproduct_strict (X h).
    -- The two formulations are definitionally equal.
    rfl
  ¬∑ rfl

/-- termF3 expanded analogously. -/
private theorem termF3_eq_sumPart (g : HopfGen) :
    termF3 g =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
          ((gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
            (coproductGen_sumPart (ő≥.contractToHopfGen
              (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥.1 hő≥Ne)))
        else 0 := by
  unfold termF3 coproductGen_sumPart
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥ _
  split_ifs with hő≥
  ¬∑ rfl
  ¬∑ rfl

/-! ### Stage 3b-ii ‚ÄĒ sigma-form double sums

`termE3` and `termF3` are each rewritten as a sum over a sigma type
`ő£ ő≥_outer ‚ąą őď-index, ő≥_inner ‚ąą (inner ambient)-index`. The ambients differ:

* termE3: inner ambient is `ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph` (the subgraph itself
  viewed as a graph)
* termF3: inner ambient is `ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen.repG` (the
  contracted graph), accessed via `contractToHopfGen`'s representative.

The sigma-form makes the bijection in Stage 3b-iii immediate. -/

/-! Inner-ambient `repG` notation: the inner index for termE3 is
`repG (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1)` (the contracted graph's chosen representative).
This is not literally `ő≥.toFeynmanGraph` due to `Quotient.out`'s choice. -/

/-- Sigma form of termE3: ő£ over (ő≥_outer, ő≥_inner) chains. -/
private theorem termE3_sigma_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    termE3 g =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥_outer ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥o : ő≥_outer.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_outer.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥oNe : ő≥_outer.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥o.2
          ‚ąĎ ő≥_inner ‚ąą (repG (ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1)).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
            if hő≥i : ő≥_inner.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_inner.internalEdges.card then
              let hő≥iNe : ő≥_inner.IsNonempty :=
                FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥i.2
              (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
                (((gen (ő≥_inner.toHopfGen hő≥i.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                  (gen (ő≥_inner.contractToHopfGen
                    (repG_wellFormed (ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1))
                    (repG_isOnePI (ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1))
                    hő≥i.1 hő≥iNe) : HopfH)) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                  (gen (ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen
                    (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1 hő≥oNe) : HopfH))
            else 0
        else 0 := by
  rw [termE3_eq_sumPart]
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥_outer _
  split_ifs with hő≥o
  ¬∑ -- Goal: assoc ((coproductGen_sumPart h_outer) ‚äó c_outer)
  --     = ő£_inner if hő≥i then assoc (...) else 0
  -- Step: expand sumPart, distribute (¬∑ ‚äó c) ‚Üí sum_tmul, then map_sum.
    simp only []
    rw [coproductGen_sumPart_eq, TensorProduct.sum_tmul, map_sum]
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro ő≥_inner _
    split_ifs with hő≥i
    ¬∑ rfl
    ¬∑ simp [TensorProduct.zero_tmul]
  ¬∑ rfl

/-- Sigma form of termF3: ő£ over (ő≥_outer, ő≥_inner_in_quotient) chains. -/
private theorem termF3_sigma_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    termF3 g =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥_outer ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥o : ő≥_outer.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_outer.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥oNe : ő≥_outer.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥o.2
          ‚ąĎ ő≥_inner ‚ąą (repG (ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen
              (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1 hő≥oNe)).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
            if hő≥i : ő≥_inner.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_inner.internalEdges.card then
              let hő≥iNe : ő≥_inner.IsNonempty :=
                FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥i.2
              ((gen (ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                ((gen (ő≥_inner.toHopfGen hő≥i.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                  (gen (ő≥_inner.contractToHopfGen
                    (repG_wellFormed (ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen
                      (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1 hő≥oNe))
                    (repG_isOnePI (ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen
                      (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1 hő≥oNe))
                    hő≥i.1 hő≥iNe) : HopfH)))
            else 0
        else 0 := by
  rw [termF3_eq_sumPart]
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥_outer _
  split_ifs with hő≥o
  ¬∑ simp only []
    rw [coproductGen_sumPart_eq, TensorProduct.tmul_sum]
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro ő≥_inner _
    split_ifs with hő≥i
    ¬∑ rfl
    ¬∑ simp [TensorProduct.tmul_zero]
  ¬∑ rfl

/-! ### Stage 3b-iii ‚ÄĒ representative-flexible sumPart equality

`coproductGen_sumPart h` is defined via the chosen representative
`repG h = Quotient.out h.val`. For the bijection in Stage 3b-iv we
need to evaluate it over an arbitrary representative `G` of `h.val`
(specifically `G = ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph` for the outer chain).

The flexibility comes from H4.6's iso-invariance applied at the
sumPart level. We package it as a single representative-flexible
lemma to avoid duplicating the proof for termE3 and termF3.

This pattern will also serve Sprint E's antipode recursion. -/

/-- **Stage 3b-iii core** ‚ÄĒ `coproductGen_sumPart h` evaluated over an
arbitrary representative `G` of `h.val`. Combines `coproductGen_sumPart_eq`
with iso-invariance (mapPermSubgraph bijection from H4.6 Phase B). -/
private theorem coproductGen_sumPart_eq_amb (h : HopfGen)
    (G : FeynmanGraph) (hWF : G.WellFormed) (hG1PI : G.IsOnePI)
    (hCD : G.IsConnectedDivergent) (hClass : G.toClass = h.val) :
    coproductGen_sumPart h =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥ ‚ąą G.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥ : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥Ne : ő≥.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥.2
          (gen (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
            (gen (ő≥.contractToHopfGen hWF hG1PI hő≥.1 hő≥Ne) : HopfH)
        else 0 := by
  -- Step 1: rewrite LHS via coproductGen_sumPart_eq ‚Üí ő£ over (repG h).toFG.
  rw [coproductGen_sumPart_eq h]
  -- Step 2: repG h has class h.val (by repG_toClass h); also hClass : G.toClass = h.val.
  -- So repG h and G are in the same class, hence IsIso.
  have hRepClass : (repG h).toFeynmanGraph.toClass = G.toClass := by
    rw [repG_toClass h, ‚Üź hClass]
  have hIso : G.IsIso (repG h).toFeynmanGraph :=
    (FeynmanGraph.toClass_eq_iff G (repG h).toFeynmanGraph).mp hRepClass.symm
  -- Step 3: use mapPermSubgraph from H4.6 to bijectively reindex.
  obtain ‚ü®ŌÄ, hŌÄ‚ü© := hIso
  -- mapPermSubgraph hŌÄ : FeynmanSubgraph G ‚Üí FeynmanSubgraph (repG h).toFG
  -- The two index sets correspond bijectively under this map.
  -- We use Finset.sum_bij in the *reverse* direction to match the goal:
  -- ő£ over (repG h)-subgraphs = ő£ over G-subgraphs (via mapPermSubgraph).
  symm
  apply Finset.sum_bij (fun ő≥ _ => mapPermSubgraph hŌÄ ő≥)
  ¬∑ -- maps-into
    intro ő≥ hő≥
    exact (mapPermSubgraph_mem_index_iff hŌÄ ő≥).mpr hő≥
  ¬∑ -- injective: same proof as H4.6 Phase B
    intro ő≥‚āĀ _ ő≥‚āā _ heq
    apply FeynmanSubgraph.ext_iff.mpr
    have hELInj : Function.Injective (ExternalLeg.map ŌÄ) := by
      intro ‚Ąď‚āĀ ‚Ąď‚āā h
      cases ‚Ąď‚āĀ with
      | mk a‚āĀ s‚āĀ =>
        cases ‚Ąď‚āā with
        | mk a‚āā s‚āā =>
          have hŌÄa : ŌÄ a‚āĀ = ŌÄ a‚āā := congrArg ExternalLeg.attachedTo h
          have hs : s‚āĀ = s‚āā := congrArg ExternalLeg.sector h
          have : a‚āĀ = a‚āā := ŌÄ.injective hŌÄa
          subst this; subst hs; rfl
    refine ‚ü®?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ have h := congrArg FeynmanSubgraph.vertices heq
      rw [mapPermSubgraph_vertices, mapPermSubgraph_vertices] at h
      exact Finset.image_injective ŌÄ.injective h
    ¬∑ have h := congrArg FeynmanSubgraph.internalEdges heq
      rw [mapPermSubgraph_internalEdges, mapPermSubgraph_internalEdges] at h
      exact Multiset.map_injective
        (FeynmanGraph.FeynmanEdge_map_injective ŌÄ) h
    ¬∑ have h := congrArg FeynmanSubgraph.externalLegs heq
      rw [mapPermSubgraph_externalLegs, mapPermSubgraph_externalLegs] at h
      exact Multiset.map_injective hELInj h
  ¬∑ -- surjective via mapPermSubgraph_preimage
    intro ő≥' hő≥'
    refine ‚ü®mapPermSubgraph_preimage hŌÄ ő≥', ?_,
      mapPermSubgraph_preimage_eq hŌÄ ő≥'‚ü©
    have := (mapPermSubgraph_mem_index_iff hŌÄ
      (mapPermSubgraph_preimage hŌÄ ő≥')).mp
    rw [mapPermSubgraph_preimage_eq] at this
    exact this hő≥'
  ¬∑ -- per-term equality: HopfGen subtype ext via mapPermSubgraph_toClass_eq.
    intro ő≥ hő≥
    have hő≥'full := (G.mem_properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs ő≥).mp hő≥
    have hő≥''full := ((repG h).toFeynmanGraph.mem_properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs
        (mapPermSubgraph hŌÄ ő≥)).mp
      ((mapPermSubgraph_mem_index_iff hŌÄ ő≥).mpr hő≥)
    have hő≥' : ő≥.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥.internalEdges.card :=
      ‚ü®hő≥'full.1, hő≥'full.2.1‚ü©
    have hő≥'' : (mapPermSubgraph hŌÄ ő≥).IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß
        0 < (mapPermSubgraph hŌÄ ő≥).internalEdges.card :=
      ‚ü®hő≥''full.1, hő≥''full.2.1‚ü©
    rw [dif_pos hő≥', dif_pos hő≥'']
    -- Zeta-reduce the let hő≥Ne inside the if-pos body.
    simp only []
    -- Both tensor factors match via Subtype.ext on toClass equality.
    have hLeft : (ő≥.toHopfGen hő≥'.1) =
        (mapPermSubgraph hŌÄ ő≥).toHopfGen hő≥''.1 :=
      Subtype.ext (mapPermSubgraph_toClass_eq hŌÄ ő≥).symm
    have hRight :
        (ő≥.contractToHopfGen hWF hG1PI hő≥'.1
          (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥'.2)) =
        ((mapPermSubgraph hŌÄ ő≥).contractToHopfGen
          (repG_wellFormed h) (repG_isOnePI h) hő≥''.1
          (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥''.2)) :=
      Subtype.ext (mapPermSubgraph_contract_toClass_eq hWF hŌÄ ő≥).symm
    rw [hLeft, hRight]

/-! ### Stage 3b-iv-pre ‚ÄĒ inner-ambient cleanup via sumPart_eq_amb

Apply `coproductGen_sumPart_eq_amb` to rewrite the inner sums in
`termE3_sigma_eq` and `termF3_sigma_eq` over the natural ambients
`ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph` and `ő≥_outer.contract`, respectively. -/

/-- termE3 with inner sum reindexed to `ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph`-subgraphs.
This makes the bijection in Stage 3b-iv possible. -/
private theorem termE3_sigma_amb_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    termE3 g =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥_outer ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥o : ő≥_outer.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_outer.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥oNe : ő≥_outer.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥o.2
          ‚ąĎ ő≥_inner ‚ąą ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
            if hő≥i : ő≥_inner.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_inner.internalEdges.card then
              let hő≥iNe : ő≥_inner.IsNonempty :=
                FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥i.2
              (Algebra.TensorProduct.assoc ‚Ąö ‚Ąö ‚Ąö HopfH HopfH HopfH).toAlgHom
                (((gen (ő≥_inner.toHopfGen hő≥i.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                  (gen (ő≥_inner.contractToHopfGen
                    ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph_wellFormed
                    hő≥o.1.isOnePI hő≥i.1 hő≥iNe) : HopfH)) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                  (gen (ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen
                    (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1 hő≥oNe) : HopfH))
            else 0
        else 0 := by
  rw [termE3_eq_sumPart]
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥_outer _
  split_ifs with hő≥o
  ¬∑ simp only []
    -- Use sumPart_eq_amb on `ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1` with `G = ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph`.
    -- The class equality is `ő≥_outer.toFG.toClass = (ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1).val` by toHopfGen_val.
    rw [coproductGen_sumPart_eq_amb (ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1)
      ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph
      ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph_wellFormed
      hő≥o.1.isOnePI
      (ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph_isConnectedDivergent hő≥o.1)
      rfl]
    rw [TensorProduct.sum_tmul, map_sum]
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro ő≥_inner _
    split_ifs with hő≥i
    ¬∑ rfl
    ¬∑ simp [TensorProduct.zero_tmul]
  ¬∑ rfl

/-- termF3 with inner sum reindexed to `ő≥_outer.contract`-subgraphs. -/
private theorem termF3_sigma_amb_eq (g : HopfGen) :
    termF3 g =
      ‚ąĎ ő≥_outer ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
        if hő≥o : ő≥_outer.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_outer.internalEdges.card then
          let hő≥oNe : ő≥_outer.IsNonempty :=
            FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥o.2
          ‚ąĎ ő≥_inner ‚ąą ő≥_outer.contract.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs,
            if hő≥i : ő≥_inner.IsConnectedDivergent ‚ąß 0 < ő≥_inner.internalEdges.card then
              let hő≥iNe : ő≥_inner.IsNonempty :=
                FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥i.2
              ((gen (ő≥_outer.toHopfGen hő≥o.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                ((gen (ő≥_inner.toHopfGen hő≥i.1) : HopfH) ‚äó‚āú[‚Ąö]
                  (gen (ő≥_inner.contractToHopfGen
                    (FeynmanSubgraph.wellFormed_contract (repG_wellFormed g))
                    (FeynmanSubgraph.contract_isOnePI (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1.isOnePI hő≥oNe)
                    hő≥i.1 hő≥iNe) : HopfH)))
            else 0
        else 0 := by
  rw [termF3_eq_sumPart]
  apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
  intro ő≥_outer _
  split_ifs with hő≥o
  ¬∑ simp only []
    -- Use sumPart_eq_amb on `ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen ...` with `G = ő≥_outer.contract`.
    -- Class equality: ő≥_outer.contract.toClass = (ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen ...).val by contractToHopfGen_val.
    rw [coproductGen_sumPart_eq_amb
      (ő≥_outer.contractToHopfGen
        (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1
        (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥o.2))
      ő≥_outer.contract
      (FeynmanSubgraph.wellFormed_contract (repG_wellFormed g))
      (FeynmanSubgraph.contract_isOnePI (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1.isOnePI
        (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥o.2))
      ?contractCD
      rfl]
    case contractCD =>
      -- ő≥_outer.contract.IsConnectedDivergent (graph level, ambient-free).
      -- `contractToHopfGen_val` gives the class equality; we need the IsCD predicate
      -- on ő≥_outer.contract directly. Use the contract preservation chain plus
      -- the subgraph‚Üígraph lift (`toFeynmanGraph_isConnectedDivergent`).
      have hSelfCD : (FeynmanSubgraph.self ő≥_outer.contract
          (FeynmanSubgraph.wellFormed_contract (repG_wellFormed g))).IsConnectedDivergent :=
        FeynmanSubgraph.contract_isConnectedDivergent
          (repG_wellFormed g) (repG_isOnePI g) hő≥o.1.isOnePI
          (FeynmanSubgraph.isNonempty_of_internalEdges_pos hő≥o.2) hő≥o.1.isDivergent
      exact (FeynmanSubgraph.self ő≥_outer.contract _).toFeynmanGraph_isConnectedDivergent hSelfCD
    rw [TensorProduct.tmul_sum]
    apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
    intro ő≥_inner _
    split_ifs with hő≥i
    ¬∑ rfl
    ¬∑ simp [TensorProduct.tmul_zero]
  ¬∑ rfl

/-! ### Stage 3b-iv-A ‚ÄĒ Subgraph ambient promotion

Given `ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph G` and `ő≥_inner : FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph`,
construct `ő≥_inner.promote ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph G` with the same
data fields but ambient changed from `ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph` to `G`.

Subset/le witnesses come from transitivity:
- `ő≥_inner.vertices ‚äÜ ő≥_outer.vertices ‚äÜ G.vertices`
- `ő≥_inner.internalEdges ‚Č§ ő≥_outer.internalEdges ‚Č§ G.internalEdges`
- `ő≥_inner.externalLegs ‚Č§ ő≥_outer.externalLegs ‚Č§ G.externalLegs`

Support fields are unchanged (vertices stays the same). -/

namespace FeynmanSubgraph

variable {G : FeynmanGraph}

/-- Promote an inner subgraph from `ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph`-ambient to
`G`-ambient. Same data fields, transitive subset/le witnesses. -/
def promote {ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph G}
    (ő≥_inner : FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph) : FeynmanSubgraph G where
  vertices := ő≥_inner.vertices
  internalEdges := ő≥_inner.internalEdges
  externalLegs := ő≥_inner.externalLegs
  vertices_subset := ő≥_inner.vertices_subset.trans ő≥_outer.vertices_subset
  internalEdges_le := ő≥_inner.internalEdges_le.trans ő≥_outer.internalEdges_le
  externalLegs_le := ő≥_inner.externalLegs_le.trans ő≥_outer.externalLegs_le
  edges_supported := ő≥_inner.edges_supported
  legs_supported := ő≥_inner.legs_supported

@[simp] theorem promote_vertices {ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph G}
    (ő≥_inner : FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph) :
    (promote (ő≥_outer := ő≥_outer) ő≥_inner).vertices = ő≥_inner.vertices := rfl

@[simp] theorem promote_internalEdges {ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph G}
    (ő≥_inner : FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph) :
    (promote (ő≥_outer := ő≥_outer) ő≥_inner).internalEdges = ő≥_inner.internalEdges := rfl

@[simp] theorem promote_externalLegs {ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph G}
    (ő≥_inner : FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph) :
    (promote (ő≥_outer := ő≥_outer) ő≥_inner).externalLegs = ő≥_inner.externalLegs := rfl

/-- The promoted subgraph's underlying `FeynmanGraph` equals the inner's. -/
@[simp] theorem promote_toFeynmanGraph {ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph G}
    (ő≥_inner : FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph) :
    (promote (ő≥_outer := ő≥_outer) ő≥_inner).toFeynmanGraph = ő≥_inner.toFeynmanGraph := rfl

end FeynmanSubgraph

/-- The nested-chain forward map used by the original coassoc bijection
attempt. It sends `(ő≥_outer, ő≥_inner ‚äā ő≥_outer)` to
`(ő≥_inner promoted to őď, ő≥_outer/ő≥_inner)` in the quotient ambient. -/
private noncomputable def coassocNestedForward (g : HopfGen)
    (p : ő£ ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph,
        FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.toFeynmanGraph) :
    ő£ ő≥_outer' : FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph,
        FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer'.contract :=
  let ő≥_outer := p.1
  let ő≥_inner := p.2
  let ő≥_innerP : FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph :=
    FeynmanSubgraph.promote (ő≥_outer := ő≥_outer) ő≥_inner
  have hle : ő≥_innerP ‚Č§ ő≥_outer := by
    refine ‚ü®?_, ?_, ?_‚ü©
    ¬∑ exact ő≥_inner.vertices_subset
    ¬∑ exact ő≥_inner.internalEdges_le
    ¬∑ exact ő≥_inner.externalLegs_le
  ‚ü®ő≥_innerP, FeynmanSubgraph.contractRestrict hle ő≥_innerP.contractedVertex‚ü©

/-! ### Stage 3b-iv-B ‚ÄĒ Sigma flattening + bijection

Both `termE3` (in sigma_amb form) and `termF3` (in sigma_amb form) are
double sums over chains `(ő≥_outer, ő≥_inner)`. Flatten each into a single
sum over the sigma type
`ő£ ő≥_outer ‚ąą index_őď, ő≥_outer.toFG.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs`
(LHS) and similarly with `ő≥_outer.contract` for RHS.

Then construct a bijection of the flattened sigma sets via:
`(ő≥_outer, ő≥_inner) ‚Ü¶ (ő≥_inner.promote, ő≥_outer.contractRestrict ő≥_inner)`.

The per-term tensor equality (third factor: H1.17 contract_chain) is
handled in Stage 3c. -/

/-- Split a finite sum into the part satisfying a predicate and its complement. -/
private theorem sum_split_by_pred {őĪ ő≤ : Type*} [AddCommMonoid ő≤]
    (s : Finset őĪ) (p : őĪ ‚Üí Prop) [DecidablePred p]
    [DecidablePred (fun a => ¬¨ p a)] (f : őĪ ‚Üí ő≤) :
    (‚ąĎ a ‚ąą s, f a) =
      (‚ąĎ a ‚ąą s.filter p, f a) + (‚ąĎ a ‚ąą s.filter (fun a => ¬¨ p a), f a) := by
  exact (Finset.sum_filter_add_sum_filter_not s p f).symm

/- The old connected-only sigma-flattening lemmas for `termE3`/`termF3`
were intentionally dropped from the compiled file.  They belonged to the
blocked pre-admissible route below, were not referenced by the current H5.8F
proof path, and their fully-expanded dependent tensor statements could exhaust
the elaborator stack in the IDE.  The active proof now proceeds through the
admissible-forest `ŌÜ` reindexing interface above. -/

/-- Split the RHS coassoc sigma index according to whether the quotient
subgraph contains the contracted vertex of the outer subgraph. The
star-containing side is the image of the nested-chain `contractRestrict`
map; the star-free side is the obstruction that requires admissible
disjoint unions. -/
private theorem rhs_sigma_split_by_star (g : HopfGen) {ő≤ : Type*}
    [AddCommMonoid ő≤]
    (f : (ő£ ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph,
            FeynmanSubgraph ő≥_outer.contract) ‚Üí ő≤) :
    (‚ąĎ p ‚ąą (repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs.sigma
              (fun ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph =>
                ő≥_outer.contract.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs),
        f p)
      =
        (‚ąĎ p ‚ąą ((repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs.sigma
              (fun ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph =>
                ő≥_outer.contract.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs)).filter
              (fun p => p.1.contractedVertex ‚ąą p.2.vertices),
          f p)
        +
        (‚ąĎ p ‚ąą ((repG g).toFeynmanGraph.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs.sigma
              (fun ő≥_outer : FeynmanSubgraph (repG g).toFeynmanGraph =>
                ő≥_outer.contract.properConnectedDivergentSubgraphs)).filter
              (fun p => p.1.contractedVertex ‚ąČ p.2.vertices),
          f p) := by
  exact sum_split_by_pred _ (fun p => p.1.contractedVertex ‚ąą p.2.vertices) f

/-! ### Stage 3b-iv-B/C + 3c ‚ÄĒ termE3 = termF3 via bijection + contract_chain

The forward bijection sends `(ő≥_outer, ő≥_inner)` (LHS chain in
`ő≥_outer.toFG`-ambient) to `(ő≥_inner.promote, ő≥_outer.contractRestrict ő≥_inner)`
(RHS chain in `(repG g).toFG`-ambient + contract-quotient ambient).

Per-term equality uses H1.17 `contract_chain`:
`(ő≥_inner.promote.contract).contract (ő≥_outer.contractRestrict ő≥_inner) = ő≥_outer.contract`
as `FeynmanGraph` (literal equality), which transports the third tensor
